In a meeting at the Mulia Hotel in Bali, Indonesia, President Biden and President Xi Jinping of China expressed their commitment to open and honest dialogue between their countries. They discussed the importance of managing differences and preventing competition from turning into conflict. Both leaders emphasized the need for cooperation on global issues such as climate change and food insecurity. President Xi highlighted the significance of the China-U.S. relationship and the responsibility of leaders to guide it in the right direction. The meeting attracted global attention, and President Xi expressed his readiness to work with President Biden to bring the relationship between their countries back to a path of healthy and stable growth.